{'contentformat': 'text/x-wiki', 'contentmodel': 'wikitext', '*': '{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Water|type2=Grass}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/GO|species=Lombre}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Water|prevnum=270|prev=Lotad|nextnum=272|next=Ludicolo|round=none}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Disambig|species=Lombre}}\n|}\n{{Pokémon Infobox\n|name=Lombre\n|jname=ハスブレロ\n|jtranslit=Hasuburero\n|tmname=Hasubrero\n|ndex=271\n|hdex=020\n|karea=Mountain\n|kdex=056\n|fbrow=133\n|obrow=244\n|typebox=1\n|type1=Water\n|type2=Grass\n|category=Jolly\n|height-ftin=3\'11"\n|height-m=1.2\n|weight-lbs=71.6\n|weight-kg=32.5\n|abilityn=d\n|ability1=Swift Swim\n|ability2=Rain Dish\n|abilityd=Own Tempo\n|egggroupn=2\n|egggroup1=Water 1\n|egggroup2=Grass\n|eggcycles=15\n|evtotal=2\n|evsd=2\n|expyield=119\n|oldexp=141\n|lv100exp=1,059,860\n|gendercode=127\n|color=Green\n|catchrate=120\n|body=12\n|pokefordex=lombre\n|generation=3\n|friendship=70\n}}\n\'\'\'Lombre\'\'\' ([[List of Japanese Pokémon names|Japanese]]: \'\'\'ハスブレロ\'\'\' \'\'Hasubrero\'\') is a dual-type {{2t|Water|Grass}} {{OBP|Pokémon|species}} introduced in [[Generation III]].\n\nIt [[Evolution|evolves]] from {{p|Lotad}} starting at [[level]] 14 and evolves into {{p|Ludicolo}} when exposed to a [[Water Stone]].\n\n==Biology==\nLombre is a bipedal Pokémon that is mostly green with some light blue markings. Its face, ears, arms, and back are light blue. It has stubby, round ears, large eyes with small pupils, and a red bill-like mouth. There is a large lilypad on its head, which has a notch in it and resembles a sombrero. It has long arms with four red fingers and a thumb on each hand and feet with three toes. Its entire body is covered in a thin, slimy film that creates an unpleasant sensation when touched. It is sometimes mistaken for a human child.\n\nLombre is a nocturnal Pokémon that sleep on a {{DL|List of Pokémon by habitat|Water\'s-edge Pokémon|bed of water grass}} during the day. Very mischievous, this Pokémon will tug on fishing lines from underwater and pop out to startle people. It feeds on aquatic moss that grows on rocks in the riverbed.\n\n==In the anime==\n[[File:Lombre DP139.png|thumb|left|250px|Lombre in the {{pkmn|anime}}]]\n===Major appearances===\n====[[Brock\'s Lombre]]====\n{{an|Brock}}\'s {{p|Lotad}} evolved into Lombre in \'\'[[AG063|Take the Lombre Home]]\'\'. The people in the village {{Ash}} and {{ashfr}} were visiting claimed that Lombre would bring water back to their village. Lombre evolved into {{p|Ludicolo}} in \'\'[[AG105|Once in a Mawile]]\'\'.\n\n====Other====\nA {{pkmn2|wild}} Lombre appeared in \'\'[[DP139|A Faux Oak Finish!]]\'\', where {{an|Professor Oak}} gave it a [[Water Stone]] to evolve.\n\nMultiple Lombre appeared in \'\'[[XY056|One for the Goomy!]]\'\', after being startled by Team Rocket when {{TP|James|Inkay}} attacked the river with {{m|Psybeam}}. They subsequently attacked Team Rocket and Ash\'s group using {{m|Bubble Beam}} along with {{p|Lotad}}, who were using {{m|Energy Ball}}. This caused the groups to get separated from each other.\n\n===Minor appearances===\nA Lombre appeared in \'\'[[Pokémon Mystery Dungeon: Team Go-Getters Out of the Gate!]]\'\'.\n\nA {{pkmn|Coordinator}}\'s Lombre appeared in \'\'[[AG167|What I Did for Love!]]\'\'.\n\nA Lombre appeared in \'\'[[DP029|The Champ Twins!]]\'\'.\n\nA {{pkmn|Trainer}}\'s Lombre appeared in \'\'[[XY059|Under the Pledging Tree!]]\'\', where it was among the Pokémon present during the [[Coumarine City Festival]].\n\n===Pokédex entries===\n{{Animedexheader|Hoenn}}\n{{Animedexbody|AG063|Lombre|Ash\'s Pokédex|Lombre, the Jolly Pokémon. Lombre is the evolved form of {{p|Lotad}}. Primarily a nocturnal creature, it is sometimes mistaken for a human child.}}\n{{Animedexbody|AG087|Lombre|[[Pokémon Mystery Club]]\'s Pokédex|Lombre, the Jolly Pokémon. Lombre is the evolved form of Lotad.}}\n{{Animedexfooter/Pokémon|\'\'Advanced Generation\'\'|Hoenn}}\n{{Animedexheader|Sinnoh}}\n{{Animedexbody|DP139|Lombre|Ash\'s Pokédex|Lombre, the Jolly Pokémon. Lombre is a playful trickster. If it spots an angler, it will tug on the fishing line to interfere.}}\n{{Animedexfooter/Pokémon|\'\'Diamond & Pearl\'\'|Sinnoh}}\n\n==In the manga==\n[[File:Shelly Lombre Adventures.png|thumb|180px|Lombre in [[Pokémon Adventures]]]]\n===In the Ash & Pikachu manga===\n{{main|Brock\'s Lombre}}\n{{an|Brock}} owns a Lombre in [[Ash & Pikachu]].\n\n===In the Pokémon Adventures manga===\n{{tc|Aqua Admin}} [[Shelly]] has a Lombre that appeared in \'\'[[188|Lombre Larceny]]\'\'. She evolved it into a Ludicolo using her [[Water Stone]] whilst fighting {{adv|Sapphire}} near [[Rustboro City]].\n\nA student\'s Lombre appeared in \'\'[[PS530|Movie Panic]]\'\'.\n\nA Lombre appeared in \'\'[[PAXY33|Chesnaught Protects]]\'\' and \'\'[[PAXY34|Charizard Transforms]]\'\' as a resident of the [[Pokémon Village]].\n\nA Lombre appeared in a flashback in \'\'[[PAXY35|Yveltal Steals]]\'\'.\n\nA Lombre appeared in \'\'[[PAXY37|Zygarde Agitated]]\'\'.\n\n===In the Pokémon Pocket Monsters manga===\nA Lombre appeared in [[PMDP54]].\n\n==In the TCG==\n{{main|Lombre (TCG)}}\n\n==Game data==\n===NPC appearances===\n{{main|Lombre (Red and Blue Rescue Team)}}\n* [[Pokémon Mystery Dungeon: Red Rescue Team and Blue Rescue Team]]: Lombre hangs around [[Pokémon Square]]. Lombre appears to like its personality, as is shown through its decision not to evolve into the carefree Ludicolo. He is also present on the [[Hill of the Ancients]] to celebrate the victory of the fallen star being destroyed, and is playfully cornered by [[Team Hydro|Blastoise]] and the [[List of Pokémon Mystery Dungeon: Red Rescue Team and Blue Rescue Team characters|other NPC characters]] while the {{player}} begins to vanish. After the game is completed, he gives the player access to [[Stormy Sea]].\n* {{g|Super Mystery Dungeon}}: Another Lombre appears as a resident of [[Serene Village]].\n\n===Pokédex entries===\n{{Dex/Header|type=Water|type2=Grass}}\n{{Dex/NA|gen=III